subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species is similar to 
Symplanella brevicephala
(Chou, Yuan & Wang, 1994), but can be distinguished by: i) frons and clypeus mostly black (dark brown in 
Symplanella brevicephala
); ii) posterior margin of male pygofer having one stout spinous process at middle, directed ventro-caudad (having one stout tooth-like process dorsally, directed dorso-caudad in 
Symplanella brevicephala
); iii) genital style in lateral view dorso-apical angle broadly rounded (acutely rounded in 
Symplanella brevicephala
); iv) aedeagal shaft mostly straight (S-shaped in 
Symplanella brevicephala
).
